    usf:contractConstraint "The compiler validates registered semantic sources, derivation, SHACL, integrity, contamination, and source observations transactionally and fails closed with rollback.", "Generated projections bind the current live-authority digest and registered repository-local semantic inputs; historical source references and source digests remain provenance only and can neither establish current identity nor authorise a target architecture.", "A digest-bound model-incomplete or proof-blocked contract projection preserves claims, nonclaims, and obligations while granting no action, path, format, proof, or decision authority.", "The foundation release signing identity derives from the public hermetic label usf-foundation-release-hermetic-evaluation-key-v1 and provides deterministic integrity and tamper evidence only; it is not a production authenticity credential.".
