cap:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutes a usf:Capability;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutes";
    usf:dependsOn cap:providerconfigurationplane;
    usf:hasContract sc:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutes;
    usf:inDomain dom:developerplatform;
    usf:decisionRationale "Development and deterministic test require contract-faithful substitutes at provider ports; this boundary owns substitute behaviour and test control, while capability code remains provider-independent and production-shaped staging uses separately warranted provider modes.".
cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstituteslifecycle a usf:ContractFacet;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstituteslifecycle";
    usf:facetKind facet:lifecycle;
    usf:facetStatus <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    usf:facetStatement "Each substitute instance follows configured, ready, serving, degraded, unavailable and reset states. Configuration validation precedes readiness; reset atomically clears contract-owned state and deterministic controls; unavailable or invalid configuration fails closed. Startup, shutdown, retry, timeout and recovery transitions are observable, idempotent where repeated, and bounded by declared limits.".
cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesstatemodel a usf:ContractFacet;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesstatemodel";
    usf:facetKind facet:statemodel;
    usf:facetStatus <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    usf:facetStatement "State is isolated by provider, environment and tenant; it includes deterministic clock, randomness seed, identifiers, queued work, retry counters, idempotency keys, injected failures and provider-shaped records. Transactions expose no partial writes, concurrent operations have deterministic conflict semantics, reset cannot cross a tenant boundary, and persisted substitutes declare schema, migration, rollback, backup and restore behaviour.".
cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutespermissions a usf:ContractFacet;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutespermissions";
    usf:facetKind facet:permissions;
    usf:facetStatus <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    usf:facetStatement "Only explicitly authorised development or test automation may select, configure, seed, reset or inject failures into a substitute. Tenant identity and permission context are mandatory for tenant-scoped operations; secrets and production credentials are forbidden; cross-tenant reads, writes, reset and observation fail closed and produce auditable denials.".
cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutescontracts a usf:ContractFacet;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutescontracts";
    usf:facetKind facet:contracts;
    usf:facetStatus <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    usf:facetStatement "Every substitute implements a declared provider port and the provider-facing commands, APIs, events and error vocabulary consumed by its capability. It supplies deterministic controls for clock, seed, fixtures, reset, failure injection and observation without leaking those controls into production interfaces. Unsupported provider behaviour is an explicit nonclaim or a blocking semantic gap, never silent success.".
cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesvalidation a usf:ContractFacet;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesvalidation";
    usf:facetKind facet:validation;
    usf:facetStatus <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    usf:facetStatement "Validation covers contract conformance, positive and negative paths, typed errors, timeout and retry schedules, idempotency, concurrency, transaction rollback, persistence recovery, tenant isolation, permission denial, resource limits, deterministic replay and poisoned-host independence. Each supported provider port is compared with its declared contract; staging claims require separate production-shaped evidence.".
cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstituteserrormodel a usf:ContractFacet;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstituteserrormodel";
    usf:facetKind facet:errormodel;
    usf:facetStatus <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    usf:facetStatement "Errors distinguish invalid configuration, forbidden control access, tenant mismatch, unsupported operation, injected provider failure, timeout, retry exhaustion, idempotency conflict, concurrency conflict, persistence failure and resource exhaustion. Errors are stable, typed, non-secret-bearing and mapped to the consuming provider contract; retries occur only for explicitly retryable classes with bounded deterministic backoff.".
cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesauditmodel a usf:ContractFacet;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesauditmodel";
    usf:facetKind facet:auditmodel;
    usf:facetStatus <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    usf:facetStatement "Configuration selection, seed, reset, failure injection, permission denial, retry exhaustion and recovery emit structured events with provider, environment, tenant, actor or automation identity, correlation identifier and deterministic control digest. Logs, metrics and traces exclude secrets and private payloads while preserving enough lineage to reproduce a test execution.".
cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesreadinessmodel a usf:ContractFacet;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesreadinessmodel";
    usf:facetKind facet:readinessmodel;
    usf:facetStatus <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    usf:facetStatement "Liveness reports process responsiveness only. Readiness requires valid explicit configuration, repository-local verified inputs, initialised schema and state, reachable owned dependencies, successful self-check of reset and deterministic controls, and no production credential or undeclared host-state dependency. A substitute never satisfies production-shaped staging or live-provider readiness.".
cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesproof a usf:ContractFacet;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesproof";
    usf:facetKind facet:proof;
    usf:facetStatus <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    usf:facetStatement "Proof binds current authority, realisation decision, repository-local source and configuration digests, provider port and mode, environment, persistence schema and migration state, dependencies, deterministic replay output, failure and recovery evidence, tenant-isolation evidence and clean-clone execution. Fixtures, mocks or reference implementations alone cannot satisfy this obligation.".
cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesuisemantics a usf:ContractFacet;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesuisemantics";
    usf:facetKind facet:uisemantics;
    usf:facetStatus <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    usf:facetStatement "This capability has no product or operator user interface. Deterministic controls are restricted automation and administrative interfaces; any human-facing interface requires a separate semantic exposure decision, accessibility model and acceptance evidence.".
sc:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutes a usf:SemanticContract;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutes";
    usf:semanticLifecycleState <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>;
    usf:hasActivationState contractstate:proofblocked;
    usf:activationReason "The independently derived semantics are complete, but no current proof yet binds a repository-local implementation and deterministic development/test environments.";
    usf:declaresFacet cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstituteslifecycle, cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesstatemodel, cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutespermissions, cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutescontracts, cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesvalidation, cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstituteserrormodel, cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesauditmodel, cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesreadinessmodel, cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesproof, cf:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutesuisemantics;
    usf:asserts <urn:usf:claim:contractfaithfultestsubstitution>;
    usf:disclaims <urn:usf:nonclaim:testsubstitutionnotstagingreadiness>;
    usf:mandatoryProofObligation <urn:usf:proofobligation:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutes>;
    usf:permittedRealisationType usf:Implementation;
    usf:requiredValidation <urn:usf:validationobligation:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutes>;
    usf:contractConstraint "The capability owns reusable deterministic provider substitution semantics and controls; consuming capabilities own their business behaviour and provider ports, and provider-specific implementations remain adapters selected by a separately accepted realisation decision.", "Development and test may use only repository-local or digest-verified inputs with explicit configuration; hidden host files, caches, original-source checkouts, pre-existing databases, mutable image tags and external work-tracker state are forbidden dependencies.", "Production-shaped staging must exercise separately warranted production-shaped provider bindings; deterministic substitutes may support controlled fault injection but cannot be used to claim live-provider, staging or production readiness.".
<urn:usf:validationobligation:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutes> a usf:ValidationObligation;
    usf:canonicalName "deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutes";
    usf:validationForContract sc:deterministicdevelopmentandtestsubstitutes.
